aah-SEPH-a-lo-sist
===[[Etymology]]===

[Gr. [[akefalos|'ake`falos]] without a head + [[kystis|ky`stis]] bladder.] 

===[[Noun]]===

''(Zo&ouml;l)''

A [[larval]] [[entozo&ouml;n]] in the form of a [[subglobular]] or oval [[vesicle]], or [[hydatid]], filled with fluid, sometimes found in the tissues of man and the lower animals; -- so called from the absence of a head or visible organs on the vesicle. These cysts are the [[immature]] stages of certain [[tapeworms]]. Also applied to similar cysts of different origin.